The paper focuses on process mining methods, which are commonly used in software engineering (cs.SE) to gain knowledge about business processes. The evaluation of automated process discovery methods involves analyzing event logs (cs.CY) and using algorithms to produce business process models (cs.AI). The paper also discusses quality metrics (cs.DB) used to evaluate the effectiveness of the automated process discovery methods. Finally, the paper provides insights for improving the usability of process discovery techniques in industry, which could be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) applications in business settings.
